u- |J\u00ab\nmm cr ~rM nom\nMB V m w V Lansburgh\u2019s\u2014JUNlCM SPORTSWEAR\nI .A&rM 1\u00bb \u201dBI\\aBM \u2014Washington and l.anglev Park, fpi\nVW- _ HVtvXv i s/ A second Floor\n9 11 m ml\nai-hington, 7th, Bth and E Streets N.W, NA. 8-9800 fMir 97th year Langley Park, New Hampshire Avenue and University Blvd. East\nI\nNo Diagnosis\nSeen for State\nOs Blood Vessel\nBy the Assoc!.ted Press\nAn official of the National\nHeart Institute expressed the\nopinion today that no one can\nsay whether President Elsen\nhower had atherosclerosis\u2014a\nform of arteriosclerosis\u2014in the\nparticular blood vessel affected\nby his attack this week.\nThe doctors said that under\nexisting methods of diagnosis\nhe does not believe it possible\nto arrive at a definite conclu\nsion.\nHe added that the medical\nreports thus far have not told\nwhether a spasm or a blood clot\ncaused blockage of the particu\nlar cerebral blood vessel.\nThe President\u2019s own doctors\nsaid in their one detailed im\nport Tuesday that they had not\nbe\u00abn able to decide that issue.\nThe heart institute official\nwas asked for comment on\nstatement* by James C. Hag\nerty, White House press sec\nretary. Mr. Hagerty said yes\nterday \u201cthere is no indication\nof general arteriosclerosis in.\nthe President.\" At the tune\ntime, Mr. Hagerty said \"the\nPresident's general arterial\ncondition gives no evidence and\nhas never given any evidence\nof sclerosis, which means\nhardening of the arteries.\u201d\n\u201cThere is a difference in the\nconnotation of what a physi\ncian calls general arterioscler\nosis and what could happen in\na particular vessel.\u201d the heart\ninstitute official said.\n\u201cThe medical report is prob\nably correct in saying there\nis no general arteriosclerosis\nIn the meaning of an over-all\nchange In the blood vessels.\n\u201cWhether or not there was\nj atherosclerosis which caused\n[the blockage, has not been re\nported. That is a kind of\n[alteration in the lining of a\n[blood vessel locally.\n\u201cWhen a clot is present the\nusual circumstances are that\n'there is some underlying ath\nerosclerotic change in the ves\nsel.\n\u201cArteriosclerosis is the fam\nily name for the three different\nkinds of blood vessel disorders.\n\u201cThe particular type more\ncommonly associated with blood\nclot disorders is atherosclerosis, j\nIt may be very spotty, a local- i\nized disturbance producing a\nspotty kind of involvement of\nblood vessels.\u201d\nThe other two kinds of dis\norders are Monckeberg\u2019s scle\nrosis. in which there is a true\nhardening or calcification of\nthe large vessels, and arteriolo\nsclerosis. a type that affects j\nsmaller vessels in general and\nis often associated with high\nblood pressure or kidney dis\norders.\nMIXUP\nContinued From First Page\ndecision that Mr. Nixon would:\nhead the American delegation\nif he did not go to Parts him\nself.\nMr. Hagerty replied that the\ndecision was made \u201cin prepar\ning with the President\u201d the\nstatement which left open the\npossibility that Mr. Eisenhower\nstill might make the Paris trip.\nWould Have to Cheek\nTo the specific question of\nwhether the President was con\nsuited on the Monday an\nnouncement that \u201cit is to be\nassumed\u201d that he would not\nattend the Paris meeting, Mr.\nHagerty replied: \u201cI believe so\u2014\nbut I would hesitate to go fur\nther without checking.\u201d\nThis left up in the air the\njust who did make\nthe decision to issue the \u201cas\ni sumed\u201d announcement Tues- 1\nday afternoon. Secretary of I\nState Dulles had been at the\nWhite House Tuesday, consult\ning with Presidential Assistant\nSherman Adams. So had Mr.\nNixon. There was the possi\nbility it was a joint action on\ntheir part.\nGovernment officials gener-|\nally are accustomed to taking\nMr. Adams\u2019 word where the\nWhite House is concerned.\nVice President Nixon stood\nin for the President yesterday\nin bidding farewell at the air\nport to King Mohamed V of\nMorocco, who was leaving on\nrroRMmT!\nI IN ALEXANDRIA i\nS CENTRAL MOTOR CO. I\n1201 Oronoco St. OV. 3-1500\nALEXANDRIA\u2019S ONLY NERCURY DEALER\nIn Hie Heart of Alexandria\u20144 Blacks From King St. m\na tour of the country after\nLater yesterday Mr. Nixon\ndropped by to see Mr. Adams\nat the White House to \u201csee\nwhether there are any loose\nends that 1 can take care of.\u201d\nthree days of talks with United\nStates officials.","height":"28641","width":"18066"}}
